<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="P" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Price" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Price,</orth> 1) the sum paid for a thing, or at which it is valued: <bibl n="shak. ven 551" default="NO" valid="yes">Ven. 551</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. ado 3.3.122" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado III, 3, 122</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lll 3.139" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL III, 139</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 3.5.26" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. III, 5, 26</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 2.1.14" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A II, 1, 14</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 2.2.154" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 II, 2, 154</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.47" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 6, 47</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 79</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 2.3.79" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. II, 3, 79</bibl> <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.188" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 1, 188</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 4.3.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. IV, 3, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 4.2.54" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. IV, 2, 54</bibl>. <emph>At</emph> before it: <cit><quote>we can afford no more at such a p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. lll 5.2.223" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL V, 2, 223</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. aww 4.3.309" default="NO" valid="yes">All's IV, 3, 309</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.190" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 3, 190</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.4.252" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. III, 4, 252</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 1.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Cor. I, 1, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cor 3.3.91" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 3, 91</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.1.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 1, 199</bibl>.<lb />2) worth, value: <cit><quote>happy news of p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.3.100" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 3, 100</bibl></cit> (Pistol's speech). <emph>a pearl, whose p. hath launched above</emph> <cit><quote>a thousand ships,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 2.2.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. II, 2, 82</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>if he overhold his p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 2.3.142" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 3, 142</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.1.27" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. IV, 1, 27</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 1.1.200" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. I, 1, 200</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 1.1.11" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. I, 1, 11</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 1.1.51" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. I, 1, 51</bibl>.
<lb />3) estimation: <cit><quote>held in idle p. to haunt assemblies,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mm 1.3.9" default="NO" valid="yes">Meas. I, 3, 9</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>our rash faults make trivial p. of serious things we have,</quote> <bibl n="shak. aww 5.3.61" default="NO" valid="yes">All's V, 3, 61</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>falls into abatement and low p.</quote> <bibl n="shak. tn 1.1.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. I, 1, 13</bibl></cit>.
